  "24-9": (
    caption: [Supercoils. A typical phone cord is coiled like a DNA helix, and the coiled cord can itself coil in a supercoil. The illustration is espe- cially appropriate because an examination of phone cords helped lead Jerome Vinograd and his colleagues to the insight that many properties of small circular DNAs can be explained by supercoiling. They first detected DNA supercoiling—in small circular viral DNAs—in 1965. c24GenesAndChromosomes.indd Page 986 12/10/12 10:34 AM user-F408 c24GenesAndChromosomes.indd Page 986 12/10/12 10:34 AM user-F408 /Users/user-F408/Desktop /Users/user-F408/Desktop 986],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
